Golden Retriever Puppy breeder based out of Florida.
Headquarters Regions: Tampa Bay Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Paradise Golden Retrievers has a remarkable health legacy spanning the past 18 years. We selectively breed two to four litters annually and have successfully placed over 400 puppies in loving Florida homes. We are proud to report that we have never had a puppy or adult dog returned due to a health issue. Despite the high incidence of cancer in American Goldens, which is over 50%, we have had only one incidence of cancer in our lines. The overall rate of health issues for Paradise Golden Retrievers is less than 1%, and any issues have been correctable. We attribute this to our selective breeding practices and utilization of English Golden Retriever lines. Since 2005, we have been finding loving family homes for our "Puppies from Paradise" all over Florida. Our puppies and dogs have been placed in Tallahassee, Jacksonville, Orlando, the Florida Keys, Miami, Naples, Sarasota, and, of course, our local Tampa Bay area. Our location in Valrico, next to Brandon, is convenient for most families looking to add a Golden puppy to their lives. Recently, we have opened a second kennel on a restored, historic plantation outside of Raleigh, North Carolina, situated on 300 acres and just 30 minutes west of Greenville. Melissa Coleman, M.Ed., has been a special education teacher for 25 years before retiring and starting Paradise Golden Retrievers. She has been passionate about the breed for over 40 years, ever since hunting the fields of rural Pennsylvania with her father and experiencing the obedience and agility of a highly-skilled hunting Golden. She has been fortunate enough to witness a wide range of Golden Retriever activities, from their excellence in retrieving in the field and stream to being beloved family companions, as well as obedient and sensitive therapy and service dogs. Melissa comments, "Goldens have such huge hearts; they are also very intuitive and have an enormous desire to please their owners." Her goal is to share the joy that Goldens bring with others who also value and love the breed. For many people purchasing a puppy, they have previously owned a Golden and require little introduction to their unique qualities. To these people, we say, "Welcome back to the wonderful world of Goldens!" For those new to the breed, you are in for a treat with Golden Retrievers! They enrich lives in countless ways with their fun-loving, ball-retrieving, and water-loving personalities. Their constant Golden "smile" is a trademark!

Full Description: Industrial Press, Inc., is a privately held technical book publishing company headquartered in South Norwalk, CT. Its primary areas of business is the development of high-value technical books for engineering, technology and manufacturing. The company seeks to be a leader in "reshoring," the robust return of manufacturing to the Western Hemisphere. Industrial Press's flagship title, the Machinery's Handbook, now celebrating 100th years of continuous publication, remains unchallenged as "The Bible" in its field. Extraordinarily comprehensive yet practical and easy-to-use, this reference for mechanical and manufacturing engineers, designers, draftsmen, toolmakers, and machinists is offered in several print and digital versions. Several hundred engineering and business titles characterize Industrial Press' catalog of expert-written educational texts aimed at the manufacturing sciences. The publishing firm introduces many new titles each year, some of them fresh editions and others as brand new works. In addition to popularity with individual practitioners in the field, Industrial Press titles are found in the curriculum of trade schools, colleges and universities, and in corporate training programs. These books are available in the general market directly from the company's website (www.industrialpress.com) as well as from channel partners such as Amazon and Barnes & Noble.

Description: NexGenix Pharmaceuticals Holdings, Inc., a privately held New York biotechnology company.

Full Description: NexGenix is a privately-held drug discovery and development company focused on the "next generation" of targeted therapies for cancer and diseases of the nervous system such as glioblastoma, neurodegenerative diseases, neurofibromatosis, and autism-spectrum disorders. The Company has acquired, through in-licensing and research collaboration, a robust structural chemistry platform in resorcylic macrolides, highly potent inhibitors of the chaperone, heat shock protein 90 (Hsp90). The concept that numerous diseases, including cancer, neurofibromatosis, amyotrophic lateral sclerosis (ALS or Lou Gehrig's disease) and Parkinson's disease involve misregulation of protein homeostasis presents a unique opportunity for drug development for these varied disorders. NexGenix's novel Hsp90 inhibitors, based on the highly potent compound radicicol, exhibit the potential to be best in class drugs.
